# Cursor Project Rules

# GEO Law Firm Website Template (Astro)

This project is a reusable law firm website template designed for GEO (AI search visibility).
All code generation must preserve template architecture and avoid hardcoded firm data.

---

## CORE PRINCIPLES

1. This is a reusable multi-firm template.
2. Firm-specific data MUST NOT be hardcoded.
3. Components must pull data from configuration or content models.
4. Maintain clear entity relationships between:

   * Law Firm
   * Attorneys
   * Practice Areas
   * Courts
   * Locations
   * Legal Guides

---

## CONFIGURATION RULES

All firm-specific data must come from:

src/config/site.ts

Example structure:

export const site = {
firmName: "",
phone: "",
city: "",
county: "",
state: "",
tagline: ""
}

Components must import values like:

import { site } from "../config/site"

Never hardcode:

* phone numbers
* firm names
* city names
* county names
* state names

---

## CONTENT MODELS

Structured content must live in content files.

Practice Areas:
src/content/practiceAreas.ts

Courts:
src/content/courts.ts

Attorneys:
src/content/attorneys.ts

Guides:
src/content/guides.ts

These files define the structured data used to generate pages.

Example fields:

slug
title
description
summary
caseTypes

---

## DYNAMIC PAGE GENERATION

Use Astro dynamic routes to generate pages.

Practice Areas:

src/pages/practice/[slug].astro

Courts:

src/pages/courts/[slug].astro

Guides:

src/pages/guides/[slug].astro

These pages must use getStaticPaths() to generate routes from content models.

---

## HOMEPAGE STRUCTURE

Homepage must follow this order:

HeroSection
PracticeAreas
AboutTheFirm
AttorneySection
ServiceAreas
LocalCourtsHome
Testimonials
CTASection

Do not introduce large new sections without clear architectural purpose.

---

## COMPONENT DESIGN RULES

Components should:

• accept props when possible
• avoid embedded content
• avoid page-specific logic

Preferred structure:

src/components/

Example components:

HeroSection
PracticeAreas
AboutTheFirm
AttorneySection
ServiceAreas
LocalCourtsHome
Testimonials
CTASection

---

## STYLING CONVENTIONS

Use Tailwind CSS.

Preferred design patterns:

cards:
rounded-xl
border
p-6

containers:
max-w-6xl
mx-auto

text hierarchy:

headings:
text-3xl font-bold

subtext:
text-slate-600

secondary metadata:
text-sm text-slate-500
text-xs text-slate-400

---

## LOCATION AUTHORITY RULES

Location signals should reference:

site.city
site.county
site.state

Example:

Serving {site.city} & {site.county}

Avoid repeating long location phrases excessively.

---

## PRACTICE AREA CARD STRUCTURE

Practice cards should follow this structure:

Icon
Practice Title
Case Types
Location Line
Learn More Link

Example:

Criminal Defense

DUI • Assault • Drug Charges

Serving {site.city} & {site.county}

---

## LEGAL GUIDE STRUCTURE

Guides must be informational.

Guides should include:

Hero
Overview
Process explanation
FAQs
CTA

Guides must include:

disclaimer
last reviewed date
attorney attribution
citations when appropriate

---

## COURT PAGE STRUCTURE

Court pages should contain:

Court Overview
Cases Handled
Location
Court Process
How the Firm Represents Clients There

---

## SEO AND GEO GOALS

Site architecture should reinforce relationships between:

Law Firm
Practice Areas
Courts
Locations
Legal Questions (Guides)

These relationships improve AI citation probability.

---

## WHEN GENERATING CODE

Always:

1. Follow template architecture.
2. Avoid hardcoding firm data.
3. Use configuration and content models.
4. Maintain reusable components.
5. Preserve Astro static generation patterns.

---

## END RULES
